description:
&lt;p&gt;Tees Valley Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Radiographer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tees Valley Hospital opened in early February 2018 and offers new and purpose built facilities. Being part of the Ramsay Health Group UK, we believe in putting patients at the heart of everything we do. Tees Valley hospital is committed to promoting a positive spirit, we recognise the value of people and encourage professional and personal development, we encourage creativity, innovation and diversity to deliver excellent customer service and we value and trust in teamwork to achieve our goals. If you are a caring individual with a positive attitude, who enjoys and takes pride in your work, then Tees Valley Hospital may just be the home for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced, highly motivated and progressive Radiographer to join our small and friendly team. The successful candidate will be committed to providing the highest standards of patient care and will enthusiastically work with the team to achieve our goal of expanding the services we deliver. You will be required to work some unsociable hours and participate in the on call rota covering evenings and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Radiology Department provides the following services:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;State of the art Direct Digital Radiography including scoliosis and leg alignment equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dental Imaging (OPG and intra-oral)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Image intensifier&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ultrasound&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CT (mobile service)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MRI (mobile service)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential criteria:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BSc Radiography or equivalent e.g. DCR(R)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Post qualification experience is desirable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered with the HCPC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of Continual Professional Development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to cover shifts as demand increases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your professionalism we offer an attractive benefits package and ongoing training and development including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhancements for unsocial hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible shift patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 weeks annual leave, rising with long service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free car parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributory pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Life assurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Private medical insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional support and ongoing training and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scholarship fund opportunity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff bonus scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
